Sancho Panza is another example, the perennial companion who always comes back for you no matter what. Starbuck in "Moby Dick" also, Lord Byron probably had a buddy like that too. No one can ever say anything negative about this type of man who seems to live and breathe duty.

Windows 98 design is a lot less undignified than later OS versions, but a bit "constricting", it makes you aware you are interacting with a calculator-machine. Later 7, 10, 11 already feel as outdated as Vista, but are truly "windowlike", they don't suffocate you, allow a breath.

It's probably a good thing overall for a machine to feel like a cold machine and not an illusion or hallucination. But I think the coziness factor is important, UI should utilize furniture-like brown colors, make you feel at home, orange-red spectrum emphasized. Still eludes us.

You've heard people joke about 4chan having a /po/ papercraft and origami board that sounds sort of similar to the /pol/ far-right extreme racism and antisemitism board, but what they won't tell you is that /po/ is somehow 1000x more fucked up no matter which way you slice it

There is a thread up from literally 2016 that's about making a functional paper clock (?) and apparently you can also straight up upload full PDF files there, genuinely insane place, someone is going to end up making an origami punch card computer one day if they haven't already.

Every small community left alone for long enough eventually ends up evolving into an isolated ecosystem presenting the same "Any goonworthy anime girl origami designs?" and "Here's a PDF of instructions for building a working Enigma machine decoder out of crude paper." dichotomy.

When I was like 6 years old at my village I used to play with my older female cousin's old toys and she had one Barbie type doll that I always left on the side while playing with the rest, until one time my grandma told me the doll was crying because she was lonely and abandoned.
Afterwards I always made sure to place the doll together with the rest of the toys even if I had no desire to ever play with her. That was the day I became a #MaleFeminist and a liberal humanist.
